[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    27[0m:[38;5;10m[49m (3) **Per-cohort engagement-and-coordination-outcome-and-seam-detection-precision-and-recall-and-warm-handoff-completion-and-citation-coverage-and-equity-disparity monitoring with launch-gate discipline architecturally implicit despite recipe's own elevation as central trap, with recipe-distinct integration-coverage-disparity-as-equity-acute-metric and seam-detection-precision-and-recall-as-coordination-quality-acute-metrics and per-cohort-outcome-attribution-with-multi-window-correlation extensions.** Same chapter pattern as 11.1-11.8 Finding A1 with recipe-distinct cross-organizational and integration-coverage extensions. The recipe correctly elevates per-cohort monitoring in five separate places (Cross-Cutting Design Points, Production-Gaps, Honest Take's ninth trap on equity-blindness, Where-it-Struggles, Where-the-Field-Has-Moved equity discussion). Despite this thorough prose elevation, the architecture pattern, the diagram, and the pseudocode (Step 10F outcome-correlation iteration) do not specify per-cohort launch-gate threshold values, two-axis and three-axis cohort stratification (per-language-by-channel, per-condition-mix-by-integration-coverage, per-language-by-condition-by-social-determinant-flag), per-cohort engagement rate, per-cohort engagement-attrition rate at 30/90/180-day windows (recipe-distinct operational-risk metric: "Engagement attrition by 6 months: 25-50% (operational risk, similar to other longitudinal bots)"), per-cohort referral closure rate (recipe-distinct coordination-quality-acute), per-cohort transition-of-care completion rate (recipe-distinct coordination-quality-acute), per-cohort medication-reconciliation accuracy (recipe-distinct coordination-quality-acute), per-cohort seam-detection precision per rule (recipe-distinct: "80-95% target across rules") and per-cohort seam-detection recall per rule (recipe-distinct: "70-90% target across rules"), per-cohort seam-resolution rate, per-cohort citation-coverage rate (recipe-distinct: "95%+ as launch-gate target"), per-cohort scope-violation rate, per-cohort caregiver-burden trajectory using validated instrument (Zarit Burden Interview or similar), per-cohort avoidable-readmission rate change with attribution caveats (recipe-distinct: "5-25% relative reduction (where outcomes mature)"), per-cohort avoidable-ED-utilization rate change with attribution caveats (recipe-distinct: "5-20% relative reduction (where outcomes mature)"), per-cohort duplicate-service rate change, per-cohort patient-and-caregiver-reported coordination experience, per-cohort time-to-meaningful-engagement, per-cohort time-to-clinical-outcome-impact (multi-quarter to multi-year window), per-cohort relationship-quality signals, per-cohort tool-call-failure rate per tool, per-cohort sensitive-disclosure handling completeness (cross-organizational consent enforcement, 42 CFR Part 2, state-specific mental-health and HIV protections), per-cohort integration-coverage-disparity (recipe-distinct equity-acute: well-instrumented vs. partially-instrumented vs. poorly-instrumented patients have substantially different assistant capability), per-cohort equity-disparity flags by sex, race, age, language, social-determinant flag, and integration-coverage profile with statistical-significance flags. Recipe-acute amplification because the bot is the chapter's first cross-organizational longitudinal-coordination recipe and a coordination program that reaches disproportionately the patients who are already plugged in to the digital-tool ecosystem and well-instrumented across data sources, while missing the patients with the highest coordination needs and the most limited integration coverage, is a coordination program that exacerbates rather than reduces healthcare disparities.
