[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    31[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Voice is excellent. **Em dash count: 0** (verified via grep for the `—` character against the published draft). The 70/30 vendor balance is maintained: AWS service names appear first in the AWS Implementation section. CC voice is consistent throughout: the David-with-fragmented-care-across-four-health-systems opening grounds the engineer-explaining-something-cool register exactly. Self-deprecating expertise lands well throughout the Honest Take. Healthcare-domain accuracy is broadly consistent (HIPAA references correct; 42 CFR Part 2 reference correct; HL7 v2 ADT/ORU references correct; HL7 FHIR R4 and US Core reference correct; USCDI v3 reference correct; FHIR Bulk Data Access reference correct; SMART on FHIR reference correct; 21st Century Cures Act and Information Blocking final rule reference correct; TEFCA reference correct with Recognized Coordinating Entity framing operationally accurate; ONC certification of FHIR APIs reference correct; NCPDP SCRIPT reference correct; AHRQ Care Coordination Measures Atlas reference correct; Project RED, Care Transitions Intervention (Coleman), and Transitional Care Model (Naylor) references operationally accurate; PCMH NCQA reference correct; CMS Chronic Care Management and Transitional Care Management references correct; Zarit Burden Interview reference correct; Beers Criteria and STOPP/START references operationally accurate; FDA SaMD framework reference correct; FDA Clinical Decision Support Software 2022 final guidance reference correct; WCAG 2.1 reference correct; OWASP LLM Top 10 reference correct; TCPA and 10DLC reference correct; AMA Augmented Intelligence Resources reference correct; CMS Acute Hospital Care at Home waiver reference operationally accurate). Architectural accuracy is high. The ten-stage decomposition is the architecturally-correct shape. The Bedrock-Agents-for-tool-orchestration framing, the Bedrock-Knowledge-Bases-for-multi-corpus-RAG framing (coordinati